text: WASHINGTON The FBI has opened 160 case files in its investigation of the storming of the U.S. Capitol by rioters supporting President Donald Trump last week, the head of the agencys Washington field office said on Tuesday.The assistant director in charge of the field office, Steven DAntuono, told a media briefing that the FBI had received 100,000 videos and pictures as tips.U.S. acting Attorney Michael Sherwin said 70 cases have already been charged, and he expects that would grow into the hundreds.
